We could use a Max-Heap capped at size k and advance the index to the next row whenever the top of the max-heap is less than or equal to the element being considered. Time case complexity of k(log k)

//Code below

public int compute ( int[][] arr, int k ) {

        PriorityQueue<Integer> pq = new PriorityQueue<>((a,b) -> b-a);

        int idx = 0;

        int n = arr.length;

        while(idx < n*n) {
            int x = idx/n;
            int y = idx%n;

            if(pq.size() == k && pq.peek() <= arr[x][y]) {
                idx = (x+1)*n;
                continue;
            }

            pq.add(arr[x][y]);
            if(pq.size() > k) {
                pq.poll();
            }

            idx++;
        }

        return pq.peek();
    }

Complexity: time `O(k * logN)` and space `O(N)`.

We can use a priority queue to keep track of the current smallest numbers. 
Initially, we only have one value in the priority queue `(1, 1, 1)`, indicating that the current smallest number is 1 at row 1, col 1. 

We do the following `k - 1` times. For each iteration, we pop one element from the priority queue and insert two elements: 

1) the one directly to the right in the matrix;
2) the element directly at the bottom of the matrix if the current element is the first in the row. 

For example, when we pop `(1, 1, 1)`, we will insert `(1, 2, 2)` and `(2, 1, 2)`; when we pop `(1, 2, 2)`, we will insert `(1, 3, 3)`. 

Finally, after `k - 1` operations of the above, whatever at the top of the heap will be our answer. 

```
object Solution {
  private case class Item(row: Int, col: Int, value: Int)
  private[this] def itemOrderingByValue: Ordering[Item] = Ordering.by[Item, Int](-_.value)

  def kthSmallest(N: Int, k: Int): Int = {
    val priorityQueue = mutable.PriorityQueue[Item](Item(1, 1, 1))(itemOrderingByValue)

    for (_ <- 1 until k) {
      val item = priorityQueue.dequeue()
      if (item.value < N) {
        priorityQueue.enqueue(Item(item.row, item.col + 1, item.value + item.row))
      }
      if (item.col == 1) {
        priorityQueue.enqueue(Item(item.row + 1, 1, item.row + 1))
      }
    }

    priorityQueue.head.value
  }
}
```

